From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 12:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix SDR frame generation image format

The swapchain wrapper was creating SDR frame generation images as
VK_FORMAT_R16G16B16A16_SFLOAT and HDR images as VK_FORMAT_R8G8B8A8_UNORM.
That is inverted from the framegen backend and benchmark path, so SDR
games can initialize the layer without useful generated output.

Use RGBA8 for SDR and RGBA16F for HDR.
---
 src/context.cpp | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/context.cpp b/src/context.cpp
index 0b140af..f0d2d1d 100644
--- a/src/context.cpp
+++ b/src/context.cpp
@@ -65,8 +65,8 @@ LsContext::LsContext(const Hooks::DeviceInfo& info, VkSwapchainKHR swapchain,
     // we could take the format from the swapchain,
     // but honestly this is safer.
     const VkFormat format = conf.hdr
-        ? VK_FORMAT_R8G8B8A8_UNORM
-        : VK_FORMAT_R16G16B16A16_SFLOAT;
+        ? VK_FORMAT_R16G16B16A16_SFLOAT
+        : VK_FORMAT_R8G8B8A8_UNORM;
 
     // prepare textures for lsfg
     std::array<int, 2> fds{};
-- 
